Package org.fluentjdbc

Class DatabaseResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.fluentjdbc.DatabaseResult
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public class DatabaseResult
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    Collects together a PreparedStatement and the resulting ResultSet, as well as metaData to map column names to collect indexes from ResultSetMetaData. Use list(RowMapper), forEach(RowConsumer) and single(RowMapper) to process the ResultSet

      Functional interface for single(RowMapper) and list(RowMapper).

      • single

        @Nonnull
public <T> Optional<T> single​(DatabaseResult.RowMapper<T> mapper)
                       throws SQLException
        Call DatabaseResult.RowConsumer for the first row in the ResultSet. Should only be used where the query parameter ensure that no more than one row can be returned, ie the query should include a unique key.
        Returns:
        the mapped row. If no rows were returned, returns Optional.empty()
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if more than one row was returned
        SQLException - if the DatabaseResult.RowMapper throws
